 The thing is, we are not connected, right?

913
00:54:30,000 --> 00:54:43,000
 I think it's very important to build a network nowadays because, okay, you can be good, but if you are alone, then you won't be able to tackle all these challenges, right?

914
00:54:43,000 --> 00:54:49,000
 Civilization-threatening challenges, right, that AI poses or other things pose.

915
00:54:49,000 --> 00:54:54,000
 So I think we've got to build this network, right, of good people going together, right?

916
00:54:54,000 --> 00:55:03,000
 And for Christians, this is also a means for bringing the faith, right, of giving witness to our faith, right?

917
00:55:03,000 --> 00:55:05,000
 Hey, let's work together.

918
00:55:05,000 --> 00:55:12,000
 You're not Catholic, you're not Christian, but we want to strive towards the same good and work together.

919
00:55:12,000 --> 00:55:14,000
 And I think this is very beautiful in this time.

920
00:55:14,000 --> 00:55:27,000
 So, yes, I am optimistic, hopeful, even though I'm not very optimistic about so many things, but we have a lot to work on, and I think God will always help us.

921
00:55:27,000 --> 00:55:28,000
 That's our hope.

922
00:55:28,000 --> 00:55:29,000
 Beautiful.

923
00:55:29,000 --> 00:55:31,000
 Well, Fr. Ken Yang, thank you so much for this conversation.

924
00:55:31,000 --> 00:55:32,000
 Thank you, Ben.

925
00:55:32,000 --> 00:55:33,000
 Thank you.

926
00:55:33,000 --> 00:55:34,000
 I've enjoyed it.

